{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Microsoft Agent Framework API",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for testing all 6 phases of the Microsoft Agent Framework API built with ASP.NET Core 10.0.\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Import this file into Postman (File → Import)\n2. Start the API: `dotnet run --project MicrosoftAgentFrameworkAPI`\n3. The `base_url` collection variable is pre-set to `http://localhost:5122`\n4. Run requests in numbered order within each phase folder\n\n## Collection Variables\n- `base_url` — API server address (change if running on a different port)\n- `sessionId` — Auto-populated by the 'Create Session' requests via test scripts\n\n## Phase Overview\n| Phase | Feature | Endpoint Prefix |\n|-------|---------|----------------|\n| 1 | Basic Agent | /api/agent |\n| 2 | Agent Tools | /api/agent |\n| 3 | Multi-Turn Sessions | /api/sessions |\n| 4 | Memory & Persistence | /api/sessions/{id}/memory |\n| 5 | Workflows | /api/workflow |\n| 6 | DI Hosting | All (DI-backed) |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:5122",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the running API. Default: http://localhost:5122"
    },
    {
      "key": "sessionId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated by the Create Session request test scripts. Do not set manually."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Phase 1 — Basic Agent",
      "description": "Your First Agent (Tutorial Step 1).\n\nCreates an AIAgent backed by Azure OpenAI and exposes it over HTTP. Tests a simple Q&A and Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Run Agent — Basic Question",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"message\": \"What is the largest city in France?\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/agent/run",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "agent", "run"]
            },
            "description": "Sends a single message to the agent and receives a complete JSON response.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{ \"response\": \"Paris is the largest city in France...\" }\n```"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has \"response\" field', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('response');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.response).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response mentions Paris', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.response.toLowerCase()).to.include('paris');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Stream Agent Response (SSE)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"message\": \"Tell me a one-sentence fun fact about the Eiffel Tower.\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/agent/run-stream",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "agent", "run-stream"]
            },
            "description": "Streams the agent response as Server-Sent Events (SSE). Each token chunk is prefixed with `data: `.\n\n**Note:** Postman buffers SSE until the stream ends. To see true streaming behaviour use `curl`:\n```bash\ncurl -N -X POST http://localhost:5122/api/agent/run-stream \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"message\":\"Fun fact about Eiffel Tower\"}'\n```\n\nExpected body (example):\n```\ndata: The\ndata:  Eiffel\ndata:  Tower\n...\n```"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is text/event-stream', function () {",
                  "    var ct = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type');",
                  "    pm.expect(ct).to.include('text/event-stream');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response body contains SSE data chunks', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include('data:');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
